        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI)",
        "coverageProbability": 0.95,
        "description": "GCI computed per Celik et al. (2008) across three mesh levels. Apparent order of convergence p=1.94. GCI_fine = 2.3% for WSS, 1.8% for velocity. Monotonic convergence confirmed."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against FDA benchmark experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA benchmark experimental measurements across all 5 operating points (2000–3500 RPM, 3–7 L/min). Mean absolute relative error 8.4%. RH index < 1 for worst-case operating condition confirmed. Turbulence model: k-omega SST. Blood rheology: Carreau–Yasuda non-Newtonian model. Power-law hemolysis correlation (Giersiepen et al.) applied to scalar transport field."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-solver-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical solver verification — method of manufactured solutions",
      "description": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver module. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed (observed order 1.97). Iterative convergence criterion set at residual drop of 5 orders of magnitude. Round-off error negligible at double precision.",
